<br>
Democracy has been a farce since the constitution was written.<br>
The writers of the constitution felt that the average person was neither educated nor informed ehough to be able to make a descision on what should be made into a law or who should be in charge, thus they instituted the current voting laws to include the electoral vote.<br>
<br>
The electoral vote is so unfair that the country is no longer what we originally fought for, FREEDOM. The lack of a direct vote has made the ideals of a government by the people a farce.<br>
4 times in our past electoral voters voted against the majority of thier state, and 2 times a president with the majority of votes lost the election.<br>
<br>
In a goverenment led by old rich people how can we be an accurate representation of the people. You cant get elected to office unless you have money to run a campaign. Once a person is voted into office they run the government by cronyism. <br>
<br>
Every president we have had has been separated from the people they govern by a generation, and sometimes by 2 genrations. When we have people in charge of us who are making descision based on ideas and beliefs that dont coincide with the current change of the nation, we are doomed to forever be behind the power curve.<br>
<br>
So yes, the civil war was a farce upon the government, but nothing as bad as it has become lately. <p><a href=mailto:Dandaelus@allakhazam.com>Dandaelus Wyldheart</a>
